  "description": "¶Curriculum ¶Syllabus The Write-for-a-Month Curricula is a collection of thirty-day structured writing modules that operationalize writing as a system of self-simulation. They apply narrative theory, cognitive poetics, and constraint-based composition to guide the writer through iterative modeling of identity. Each daily module defines a constraint (formal), a prompt (semantic), and a goal (cognitive function), forming a closed loop between generative mechanism and reflective outcome.\n",
